CHÂTEAU-FUISSE
Mouilly- Fuissé
SMOKING LOON
Business Class
White Wine
Château Fuisse,
Tête de Cru, Pouilly Fuissé
2005
The cream of the crop. Château Fuissé
produced textbook wines in the great
2005 vintage. A truly versatile food
wine; its minerality underlines the salty
sea character of all fish types and
crustaceans. It's ripe fruitiness, crisp
acidity and length, allow a marriage with
spiced foods, as well as white meat.
Smoking Loon
Pinot Grigio, California
2007
The 2007 Smoking Loon Pinot Grigio
beckons with aromas of grapefruit and
fresh sliced oranges, flavours of
nectarines, mandarin oranges, limestone
and a finish of minerals and lemongrass.
An easy and refreshing wine brimming
with sunshine coast verve.
Business Class
Red Wine
Château Croizet Bages
Grand Cru, Pauillac
1996
The excellent 1996 was a catalyst for a
return to form for Croizet Bages and this
is amply shown as this wine unfurls in
your glass. Its high perfume is overlain
with dense aromas of ripe red fruit. On
the palate, a melting amalgam of cassis,
spice and truffles, with a long lingering
finish.
NoraL Rice
Norfolk Rise Shiraz
South Australia
2005
The Limestone Coast is the source for
this juicy offering. Spotlessly clean and
pure blackberry and dark plum fruit
ooze forth. Medium-bodied with a
freshness that gives it some animation.
Classic deep but easy drinking Shiraz.
